  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Insulin resistance is a key mechanism in metabolic disorders, which has also been implicated
      in the development of pulmonary hypertension. In this pilot study, the investigatorsÂ´ goal is
      to directly determine insulin sensitivity in idiopathic pulmonary arterial hypertension
      patients and to compare the results with data from healthy controls.
    </textblock>
